an and which voice you choose to carry to the heart of the crowd.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Guard the procession along the Dorsal Span and watch for saboteurs at key choke points and oath-stalls.\",\n        \"Coordinate with Brinelaw bailiffs to reroute crowds if stampede risk increases; use the Resonance Chart to anticipate dangerous rhythms.\",\n        \"Decide whether to support Siala’s unveiling of the Heart-Scale publicly or urge a private audience at the Anchor-King’s Hall.\",\n        \"Prevent a deliberate chain cut beneath the Span from causing a collapse; apprehend the culprits if possible.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Siala Nerm\", \"lines\": \"If we hide our heart for fear of greed, we make a tomb of our city, and we salt it with our own doubts until nothing grows. I will unveil the Scale because the living deserve a true song, and because the dead do not ask us to whisper when we can sing. You know the Span as a hunter knows a ridge, Mara Kestrel; if you walk beside our banners, I will trust your hand to make space where awe will press like tide against rock. I do not ask you to believe as I do, only to listen for the beat beneath the noise, and give it room to be heard without crushing the small or the slow. Stand with me and I will owe you a debt I will not repay with words alone, but with shelter when storm comes, with Pilgrim hands when yours grow tired, and with a promise that I will not spend your courage for spectacle. Stand against me, and I will still sing for your safe road home, and I will sit with you after in the Cathedral’s hush to hear why your fear has more weight than my hope, and I will not call you faithless for fearing the crush of a crowd. If the Scale proves false, hold me publicly to the Brinelaw for deceiving hearts, for I will have deceived my own as well; but if it proves true, let us not chain the moment under ledgers and locks lest the song sour in the throat. The heart of a city 